African Eagle Resources’ Zambian Unit to Sell Shares on Lusaka Exchange

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-06-15T13:43:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/african-eagle-resources-zambian-unit-to-sell-shares-on-lusaka-exchange.html
Cobra Copper Ltd., the Zambian unit
of  African Eagle Resources Plc (AFE) , plans to sell shares on the
Lusaka Stock Exchange, Chris Davies, the company’s operations
director, said.  Cobra also plans to explore for iron ore in the southern
African country, Davies said in a speech in Lusaka, the capital,
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
